Overview:
This codebase provides code for a model and a view to run a game of Three Trios. Three Trios is a
game where two players compete to gain control of a game board using cards with different values.
These cards have directional attributes that contain numerical values that are compared with other
values adjacent to that direction in order to capture territory and convert the opponents cards.
This codebase includes a Model for managing game data, rules, and moves. It also includes a View
for rendering the current game state. A controller will be implemented soon.

Quick start:

@Test
public void testCodeBase() {

    IThreeTriosModel model = new ThreeTriosModel(
                new Random(1),
                "NoHolesBoard",
                "17Cards");

    ThreeTriosView view = new ThreeTriosView(model, new StringBuilder());

    System.out.print(view);

    model.placeCard(0, 0, 0);
}

Key components:

So far, there are two major components in this codebase: the model and the view. The model contains
two interfaces: Cell and IThreeTriosModel. IThreeTriosModel holds all the methods required to manage
player actions and card battles in a game of Three Trios. The Cell interface represents an cell on
grid of the game. A cell can either be a hole (No card can be placed there) or a CardCell
(A card can be placed there), and these are used by the model to create a playable game grid and
ensure the game is played according to the grid. There are also two Players in the Model, and these
are represented by a Player class that contains the Player's color and deck of cards that are dealt
by the model. The View contains a class that uses the data from the model to create the game state
as a string that is then appended to an appendable printed to the user.

Key subcomponents:

Model Subcomponents:
ThreeTriosModel: Main game logic.
Player: Manages cards in each player’s hand.
Card, Cell, CardCell: Represent game pieces and spaces.
Reader: Utility class for loading grid and card data from files.

View Subcomponents:
ThreeTriosView: Manages rendering game state.

Source organization:

cs3500.threetrios.model: Contains all model classes, including
                         ThreeTriosModel, Player, Card, Cell, and Reader.
cs3500.threetrios.view: Houses view classes responsible for displaying the game.
